------ REVIEW SUMMARY ------

Overall: ACCEPTABLE — no blocking issues found. Minor improvements noted.

------ REVIEW FINDINGS ------

1. [LOW] face_embedder.py — fallback resize to 112×112 may discard quality.
   Suggestion: Log a warning when fallback is triggered so the user knows.
   
2. [LOW] app.py — MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH (16 MB) is per-request, not per-file.
   Two files submitted together count together. This is fine for face photos.

3. [MEDIUM] comparator.py — threshold default 0.40 is appropriate for buffalo_sc.
   However, the value is hardcoded in two places (DEFAULT_THRESHOLD and verify()).
   Suggestion: Import DEFAULT_THRESHOLD inside verify() directly — already done ✓

4. [LOW] logger.py — CSV append mode may produce duplicate headers if the file
   is manually edited between runs. Current _ensure_header() check is safe.

5. [LOW] utils.py — cleanup_file() silences all OSError. Consider at least
   logging these errors in debug mode to aid troubleshooting.

6. [LOW] index.html — btn-text span referenced by ID ("btnText") in JS but
   the selector used is ".btn-text" class. Both selectors present; no bug.

7. [MEDIUM] app.py — no CSRF protection on POST /verify.
   Acceptable for a local tool; add flask-wtf if exposing externally.

8. [LOW] Security — uploads/ directory is never served publicly (no static route),
   so uploaded images cannot be accessed after cleanup. ✓ Good.

